Glyptagnostus reticulatus

and 

Lejopyge laevigata

have done in defining the bases of subjacent Cambrian stages. The biostratigraphic utility of 

Lotagnostus
species

with short stratigraphic ranges has been demonstrated in various areas of Asia (Lu & Lin, 1980,1989; 

